public interface ISysDBRProcedureParameter
extends ISysProcedureParameter

ISysDBRProcedureParameter is an extra interface for stored procedure calling classes to set the OUT parameter results after stored procedure execution on database.

Method Detail

setOutParameterObject

public void setOutParameterObject(int parameterIndex,
                                  Object parameterObject)
                           throws IndexOutOfBoundsException
Sets the OUT parameter value object parameterObject of ordinal position parameterIndex. This method is normally not used by yourself. The class calling the stored procedure uses it to set the values, returned by called stored procedures through OUT parameter.

Parameters:
parameterIndex - the first parameter is 1, the second is 2, and so on
parameterObject - value returned by stored procedure
Throws:
IndexOutOfBoundsException - if parameterIndex is not set.
